    <item>
      <title>Running MPI Jobs</title>
      <link>https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/mpi-jobs/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/mpi-jobs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The default sind-node image ships with a full MPI stack (OpenMPI, PMIx, PRRTE, UCX) and Slurm configured with &lt;code&gt;MpiDefault=pmix&lt;/code&gt;. This guide walks through compiling and running a simple MPI program across multiple nodes.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h2 id=&#34;create-a-multi-node-cluster&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;        Create a multi-node cluster&#xA;    &lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/mpi-jobs/#create-a-multi-node-cluster&#34; class=&#34;gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; title=&#34;Anchor to: Create a multi-node cluster&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor to: Create a multi-node cluster&#34; href=&#34;#create-a-multi-node-cluster&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Create a cluster with 3 workers:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sind create cluster &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;#39;EOF&amp;#39;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;kind: Cluster&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;nodes:&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;  - controller&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;  - worker: 3&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;EOF&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h2 id=&#34;verify-the-mpi-stack&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;        Verify the MPI stack&#xA;    &lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/mpi-jobs/#verify-the-mpi-stack&#34; class=&#34;gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; title=&#34;Anchor to: Verify the MPI stack&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor to: Verify the MPI stack&#34; href=&#34;#verify-the-mpi-stack&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Check that OpenMPI is installed and configured with PMIx and UCX:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>MCP Integration</title>
      <link>https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/mcp/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/mcp/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;sind includes a built-in &lt;a&#xA;  class=&#34;gdoc-markdown__link&#34;&#xA;  href=&#34;https://modelcontextprotocol.io/&#34;&#xA;&gt;Model Context Protocol&lt;/a&gt; (MCP) server that exposes all CLI commands as tools for AI assistants. This lets tools like Claude, VS Code Copilot, or Cursor create clusters, check status, manage workers, and control node power states through natural language.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h2 id=&#34;quick-setup&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;        Quick setup&#xA;    &lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/mcp/#quick-setup&#34; class=&#34;gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; title=&#34;Anchor to: Quick setup&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor to: Quick setup&#34; href=&#34;#quick-setup&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Register sind with your editor:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Claude Desktop&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sind mcp claude &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;enable&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# VS Code&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sind mcp vscode &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;enable&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Cursor&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sind mcp cursor &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;enable&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To unregister:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>CI/CD</title>
      <link>https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/ci-cd/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/ci-cd/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h2 id=&#34;github-action&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;        GitHub Action&#xA;    &lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/ci-cd/#github-action&#34; class=&#34;gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; title=&#34;Anchor to: GitHub Action&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor to: GitHub Action&#34; href=&#34;#github-action&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a&#xA;  class=&#34;gdoc-markdown__link&#34;&#xA;  href=&#34;https://github.com/GSI-HPC/sind-action&#34;&#xA;&gt;sind-action&lt;/a&gt; GitHub Action installs sind and creates clusters in your workflow. sind runs rootless on standard &lt;code&gt;ubuntu-latest&lt;/code&gt; runners — no privileged containers or custom runner images required.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;See the &lt;a&#xA;  class=&#34;gdoc-markdown__link&#34;&#xA;  href=&#34;https://github.com/GSI-HPC/sind-action#readme&#34;&#xA;&gt;sind-action documentation&lt;/a&gt; for inputs, outputs, cluster definitions, and examples including parallel job isolation via realms.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;h2 id=&#34;other-ci-systems&#34;&#xA;    &gt;&#xA;        Other CI systems&#xA;    &lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a data-clipboard-text=&#34;https://gsi-hpc.github.io/sind/next/guides/ci-cd/#other-ci-systems&#34; class=&#34;gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center&#34; title=&#34;Anchor to: Other CI systems&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor to: Other CI systems&#34; href=&#34;#other-ci-systems&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg class=&#34;gdoc-icon gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;use xlink:href=&#34;#gdoc_link&#34;&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;sind works in any CI environment that provides Docker. Install the binary from a &lt;a&#xA;  class=&#34;gdoc-markdown__link&#34;&#xA;  href=&#34;https://github.com/GSI-HPC/sind/releases&#34;&#xA;&gt;GitHub release&lt;/a&gt; and run &lt;code&gt;sind doctor&lt;/code&gt; to verify prerequisites:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
